[[File:Chaco_Anasazi_ladle_NPS.jpg|thumb]]出土的公元前10世纪的汤勺]]

'''勺子'''是一种有柄的可以舀取东西的器具<ref>{{cite web |title=勺的解释 |url=https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E5%8B%BA |website=汉典 |accessdate=2020-11-13 |archive-date=2020-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114034547/https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E5%8B%BA |dead-url=no }}</ref>。用于盛[[汤|汤]]的称为“汤勺”，用于舀饭的称为“饭勺”，用于炒菜的称为“炒勺”，有许多小孔的勺子称为“漏勺”。
==材料==
与其他厨具类似，现代社会中的汤勺通常是由[[不鏽鋼|不鏽鋼]][[合金|合金]]制成，但有的也会用[[铝|铝]]、[[銀|銀]]、[[塑料|塑料]]、[[三聚氰胺-甲醛树脂|三聚氰胺-甲醛树脂]]、[[木材|木材]]、[[竹|竹子]]等其他材料制作而成。

古代的勺子常常是用[[葫芦|葫芦]]、海贝等物品制成<ref>{{Cite web|title = Dippers|url = http://www.horniman.ac.uk/collections/browse-our-collections/authority/term/identifier/term-503990|accessdate = 2015-07-20|first = |last = |publisher = Horniman Museum and Gardens|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150721215302/http://www.horniman.ac.uk/collections/browse-our-collections/authority/term/identifier/term-503990|archive-date = 2015-07-21|dead-url = yes}}</ref>，称为“瓢”，如“酒瓢”、“汤瓢”等<ref>{{cite web |title=瓢的解释 |url=https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E7%93%A2 |website=汉典 |accessdate=2020-11-13 |archive-date=2020-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116161216/https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E7%93%A2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
==应用==
汤勺因用途不同而大小不一。比如，有的汤勺不到{{convert|5|inch|cm}}，用来处理调味酱；也有的汤勺大到{{convert|15|inch|cm}}，用来处理汤或者[[賓治酒|賓治酒]]。<ref>{{cite book|last=Von Drachenfels|first=Suzanne|title=The Art of the Table: A Complete Guide to Table Setting, Table Manners, and Tableware|url=https://archive.org/details/artoftable00suza|date=2000-11-09|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn= 978-0684847320|page=[https://archive.org/details/artoftable00suza/page/213 213]}}</ref>

汤勺是用来盛[[汤|汤]]、[[濃湯|濃湯]]等食品的[[勺子|勺子]]。<ref>{{cite book|last=Swartz|first=Oretha D.|title=Service although not actually a spoon as is commonly found on a table, serving spoons are grouped under the 'utensil' umbrellaEtiquette|url=https://archive.org/details/serviceetiquette00swar|edition=4th|date=1988-10-02|publisher=United States Naval Institute|isbn=978-0870216206|page=[https://archive.org/details/serviceetiquette00swar/page/228 228]}}</ref>汤勺的设计大同小异，通常有着长长的勺柄，末端则是碗状的头部，用来将液体从锅等容器中转移至[[碗|碗]]。有的汤勺的边缘会有个小凸起，以便精细控制汤的流量，但这也会为[[左利手|左利手]]者带来不便，为此有的汤勺会设计成两边都有突起的样式。

